    <keyword>gamma</keyword>
    <short_description>Gamma special function</short_description>
    <syntax>
        <syntax_item>R = gamma(M)</syntax_item>
    </syntax>
    <param_input>
        <param_input_item>
            <param_name>M</param_name>
            <param_description
      >a real single or real double matrix.</param_description>
        </param_input_item>
    </param_input>
    <param_output>
        <param_output_item>
            <param_name>R</param_name>
            <param_description>result of gamma function.</param_description>
        </param_output_item>
    </param_output>
    <description>
        <p>
            <b>gamma</b> computes the gamma function.
        </p>
        <p>The gamma function is defined by the integral:</p>
        <latex>\Gamma(z) = \int_0^{\infty} t^{z-1} e^{-t} \, dt</latex>
        <p>for</p>
        <latex>\text{Re}(z) > 0</latex>
        <p
    >The gamma function extends the factorial function to real and complex numbers:</p>
        <latex>\Gamma(n) = (n-1)!</latex>
        <p>for positive integers</p>
        <latex>n</latex>
        <p>Key properties include:</p>
        <ul>
        <li><latex>\Gamma(z+1) = z\Gamma(z)</latex> (recurrence relation)</li>
        <li><latex>\Gamma(1/2) = \sqrt{\pi}</latex></li>
        </ul>
    </description>
